Mon. 23
Run on: Two independent clauses improperly joined together 
Two types: 1.Fused: no punctuation mark between independent clauses 2.Comma Splice: comma only separating two independent clau.
Ex. Mark is a good cook but sometimes he forgets to cook enough
Four ways to correct a run on:
1. Period captial
2. Comma FANBOYS (creates compound)
3. Semicolon
4. Make one clause dependent 
